574
00:33:56,200 --> 00:33:57,500
JUST TELL ME
WHAT'S HAPPENING.

575
00:33:57,700 --> 00:33:59,400
GOT TO GO, SIR.
WE'RE REMODELING.

576
00:33:59,600 --> 00:34:00,000
NO, YOU'RE NOT.

577
00:34:00,200 --> 00:34:01,700
WHAT ARE THOSE PEOPLE
DOING BACK THERE?

578
00:34:01,900 --> 00:34:02,500
IT'S NONE OF
YOUR BUSINESS.

579
00:34:02,700 --> 00:34:05,400
IF YOU DON'T TELL ME WHAT'S
HAPPENING, I'LL REPORT YOU!

580
00:34:05,600 --> 00:34:08,000
YOU'RE TRESPASSING.

581
00:34:08,700 --> 00:34:11,000
RIGHT.

582
00:34:39,100 --> 00:34:40,700
MARLON!

583
00:34:40,900 --> 00:34:41,500
TRUMAN.

584
00:34:41,700 --> 00:34:42,400
WHAT ARE YOU
DOING HERE?

585
00:34:42,600 --> 00:34:43,500
[WHISPERING]
I gotta talk to you.

586
00:34:43,700 --> 00:34:45,000
IT'S A BAD TIME, OK?
I'M WAY BEHIND.

587
00:34:45,200 --> 00:34:48,100
I'M ONTO SOMETHING, MARLON.
SOMETHING BIG.

588
00:34:48,500 --> 00:34:49,300
YOU OK?
YOU LOOK LIKE SHIT.

589
00:34:49,500 --> 00:34:51,500
I THINK I'M MIXED UP
IN SOMETHING.

590
00:34:51,700 --> 00:34:52,000
MIXED UP IN WHAT?

591
00:34:52,200 --> 00:34:53,200
THERE'S NO POINT
TRYING TO EXPLAIN IT,

592
00:34:53,400 --> 00:34:56,400
BUT A LOT OF STRANGE THINGS
HAVE BEEN HAPPENING.

593
00:34:56,400 --> 00:34:58,700
[STAMMERING]

594
00:35:00,600 --> 00:35:02,600
THE PEOPLE ON THE ELEVATOR.

595
00:35:02,800 --> 00:35:04,200
THERE WAS
NO BACKING ON IT.

596
00:35:04,400 --> 00:35:06,200
I LOOKED OUT.
THERE WAS PEOPLE THERE.

597
00:35:06,400 --> 00:35:08,700
AND ON THE RADIO
ON THE WAY TO WORK,

598
00:35:08,900 --> 00:35:10,100
IT STARTS
FOLLOWING ME ALONG,

599
00:35:10,300 --> 00:35:12,100
TALKING ABOUT EVERYTHING
THAT I'M DOING.

600
00:35:12,300 --> 00:35:12,800
YOU KNOW WHAT I MEAN?

601
00:35:13,000 --> 00:35:15,100
TRUMAN, LOOK, THIS IS
ONE OF YOUR FANTASIES.

602
00:35:15,300 --> 00:35:16,700
I THINK
THIS IS ABOUT MY DAD.

603
00:35:16,900 --> 00:35:17,900
YOUR DAD?

604
00:35:18,100 --> 00:35:18,900
I THINK HE'S ALIVE.

605
00:35:19,100 --> 00:35:21,500
YEAH. I'LL TELL YOU
ABOUT IT LATER.

606
00:35:21,700 --> 00:35:23,400
I'm definitely
being followed.

607
00:35:23,700 --> 00:35:25,900
WHO?

608
00:35:26,500 --> 00:35:27,700
IT'S HARD TO TELL.

609
00:35:27,900 --> 00:35:30,800
THEY LOOK JUST LIKE
REGULAR PEOPLE.

610
00:35:34,000 --> 00:35:34,800
HOW ABOUT THOSE TWO?

611
00:35:35,000 --> 00:35:36,500
Truman: I DON'T KNOW.

612
00:35:36,800 --> 00:35:37,000
COULD BE.

613
00:35:37,300 --> 00:35:40,300
It's when I'm unpredictable,
that's--they can't...

614
00:35:43,500 --> 00:35:44,800
Did anything happen?

615
00:35:45,000 --> 00:35:45,200
NO.

616
00:35:45,400 --> 00:35:47,500
Mm-hmm. We gotta
get out of here.

617
00:35:47,700 --> 00:35:48,200
You ready to go?

618
00:35:48,400 --> 00:35:49,700
No. I just
came here. Come on.

619
00:35:49,900 --> 00:35:50,900
I TOLD YOU I CAN'T.

620
00:35:51,100 --> 00:35:53,400
[GROWLS]

621
00:35:55,200 --> 00:35:58,100
YOU'RE GONNA GET BOTH OUR ASSES
FIRED. YOU KNOW THAT.

622
00:35:58,300 --> 00:35:59,900
OK, MAN,
LET'S DO IT.

623
00:36:00,100 --> 00:36:01,600
WHAT?
WHATEVER YOU SAY.

624
00:36:01,800 --> 00:36:02,600
I'M GAME.

625
00:36:02,800 --> 00:36:03,600
Marlon: WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

626
00:36:03,800 --> 00:36:06,800
YES, SIREE. YOUR BIRTHDAY
COMES BUT ONCE A YEAR.

627
00:36:09,800 --> 00:36:12,500
Truman: MAYBE I'M BEING
SET UP FOR SOMETHING.

628
00:36:12,700 --> 00:36:15,500
YOU EVER THINK
ABOUT THAT, MARLON?

629
00:36:15,600 --> 00:36:16,500
LIKE YOUR WHOLE LIFE

630
00:36:16,700 --> 00:36:19,100
HAS BEEN BUILDING
TOWARDS SOMETHING?

631
00:36:19,300 --> 00:36:20,600
MMM, NO.

632
00:36:20,800 --> 00:36:22,400
WHEN YOU WERE
HAULING CHICKENS

633
00:36:22,600 --> 00:36:24,400
IN THE SUMMER
FOR KAISER,

634
00:36:24,600 --> 00:36:25,800
WHAT WAS
THE FURTHEST

635
00:36:26,100 --> 00:36:28,100
YOU EVER GOT
OFF THE ISLAND?

636
00:36:28,300 --> 00:36:29,500
WENT ALL OVER.

637
00:36:29,700 --> 00:36:32,600
NEVER FOUND A PLACE
LIKE THIS, THOUGH.

638
00:36:32,900 --> 00:36:34,500
LOOK AT THAT SUNSET,
TRUMAN.

639
00:36:34,700 --> 00:36:36,500
IT'S PERFECT.

640
00:36:36,700 --> 00:36:38,600
YEAH.

641
00:36:38,800 --> 00:36:40,900
THAT'S THE BIG GUY.

642
00:36:41,200 --> 00:36:43,400
QUITE A PAINTBRUSH
HE'S GOT.

643
00:36:43,700 --> 00:36:45,900
YUP.

644
00:36:47,900 --> 00:36:50,700
JUST BETWEEN YOU
AND ME, MARLON...

645
00:36:52,100 --> 00:36:54,700
I'M GOING AWAY
FOR A WHILE.

646
00:36:55,300 --> 00:36:57,200
REALLY?

647
00:36:57,500 --> 00:36:58,400
YEAH.

648
00:36:58,600 --> 00:37:01,300
Mother: OH, LITTLE ANGEL.

649
00:37:01,800 --> 00:37:04,200
[WOMEN LAUGH]

650
00:37:06,900 --> 00:37:09,300
OH, MY LITTLE CLOWN.

651
00:37:12,000 --> 00:37:13,300
OLD CARROT TOP.

652
00:37:13,500 --> 00:37:15,900
THE BEST PHOTOS.

653
00:37:17,400 --> 00:37:18,100
OHH.
OHH.

654
00:37:18,300 --> 00:37:19,900
WE SHOULD BE GETTING YOU
HOME, MOTHER.

655
00:37:20,100 --> 00:37:23,000
HOLD ON A MINUTE.
HERE'S US AT MOUNT RUSHMORE.

656
00:37:23,200 --> 00:37:25,700
DO YOU REMEMBER, TRUMAN,
WHEN DAD WAS STILL WITH US?

657
00:37:25,900 --> 00:37:27,300
THAT WAS QUITE A DRIVE.

658
00:37:27,500 --> 00:37:30,300
YOU SLEPT
THE WHOLE WAY THERE.

659
00:37:30,300 --> 00:37:31,300
Truman:
IT LOOKS SO SMALL.

660
00:37:31,500 --> 00:37:34,100
THINGS ALWAYS DO
WHEN YOU LOOK BACK, DARLING.

661
00:37:34,300 --> 00:37:34,900
OH, LOOK, TRUMAN.

662
00:37:35,100 --> 00:37:37,800
THE HAPPIEST DAY
OF OUR LIVES.

663
00:37:39,900 --> 00:37:41,000
OH, LOOK.

664
00:37:41,200 --> 00:37:43,100
JEAN, JODIE, JOANNE.

665
00:37:43,300 --> 00:37:44,900
DOESN'T SHE LOOK
BEAUTIFUL, TRUMAN?

666
00:37:45,100 --> 00:37:46,800
WELL, SHE STILL DOES.

667
00:37:47,000 --> 00:37:50,100
AND THERE'S LOTS OF PAGES
LEFT OVER FOR BABY PHOTOS.

668
00:37:51,300 --> 00:37:54,300
I WOULD LIKE TO HOLD
A GRANDCHILD IN MY ARMS

669
00:37:54,600 --> 00:37:54,900
BEFORE I GO.

