00:43:03,700 --> 00:43:04,200
HOW CAN I HELP?

757
00:43:04,400 --> 00:43:06,500
I WOULD LIKE TO BOOK
A FLIGHT TO FIJI.

758
00:43:06,700 --> 00:43:09,500
WHEN WOULD YOU LIKE
TO LEAVE?

759
00:43:12,200 --> 00:43:14,500
TODAY.

760
00:43:24,800 --> 00:43:26,800
[BEEP]

761
00:43:27,000 --> 00:43:27,800
[BEEP]

762
00:43:28,100 --> 00:43:30,400
[BEEP]

763
00:43:30,400 --> 00:43:31,100
I'M SORRY.

764
00:43:31,300 --> 00:43:34,300
I DON'T HAVE ANYTHING
FOR AT LEAST A MONTH.

765
00:43:35,000 --> 00:43:35,800
A MONTH?

766
00:43:36,000 --> 00:43:38,500
IT'S THE BUSY SEASON.

767
00:43:39,900 --> 00:43:41,300
YOU WANT TO BOOK THE FLIGHT?

768
00:43:41,500 --> 00:43:43,500
IT DOESN'T MATTER.

769
00:43:43,700 --> 00:43:46,500
I'LL MAKE OTHER
ARRANGEMENTS, OK?

770
00:43:49,700 --> 00:43:52,300
Man:
LAST CALL FOR CHICAGO!

771
00:43:53,500 --> 00:43:55,900
ALL ABOARD!

772
00:43:59,100 --> 00:44:00,900
[WHISTLES]

773
00:44:01,100 --> 00:44:03,400
THANK YOU.

774
00:44:05,300 --> 00:44:07,900
WINDY CITY, HERE WE COME.

775
00:44:09,100 --> 00:44:11,400
HI.
HI.

776
00:44:13,200 --> 00:44:14,800
HELLO.

777
00:44:15,000 --> 00:44:17,200
HI.

778
00:44:17,400 --> 00:44:18,400
Truman: SISTERS.

779
00:44:18,600 --> 00:44:21,100
HEY, MOM, ISN'T THAT--

780
00:44:21,600 --> 00:44:24,200
Mom: SHH.
FACE THE FRONT.

781
00:44:32,500 --> 00:44:34,900
[GEARS GRIND]

782
00:44:38,200 --> 00:44:40,600
[GEARS GRIND]

783
00:44:44,200 --> 00:44:46,100
[GEARS GRIND]

784
00:44:46,300 --> 00:44:47,900
[ENGINE STALLS]

785
00:44:48,100 --> 00:44:49,400
[RADIATOR HISSING]

786
00:44:49,600 --> 00:44:52,400
EVERYBODY OFF.
WE'VE GOT A PROBLEM.

787
00:45:12,000 --> 00:45:14,500
I'M SORRY, SON.

788
00:45:27,000 --> 00:45:29,100
HIS FATHER WAS FROM
CHICAGO, WASN'T HE?

789
00:45:29,300 --> 00:45:31,700
NO. HIS DENTIST
WAS FROM PENSACOLA.

790
00:45:31,900 --> 00:45:33,200
HIS FATHER
WAS FROM DES MOINES.

791
00:45:33,400 --> 00:45:35,300
BUT HOW COME HE WANTS
TO GO TO CHICAGO?

792
00:45:35,500 --> 00:45:38,600
HE'S NOT GOING TO CHICAGO.
HE'S NOT GOING ANYWHERE.

793
00:45:38,800 --> 00:45:41,400
  HE HAS TO HAVE IT OUT
WITH MERYL.

794
00:45:41,600 --> 00:45:44,000
[PLUTO BARKS]

795
00:45:57,000 --> 00:45:59,200
TRUMAN?

796
00:46:03,100 --> 00:46:05,600
HONEY, ARE YOU OK?

797
00:46:05,800 --> 00:46:08,100
GET IN.

798
00:46:10,300 --> 00:46:12,600
TRUMAN.

799
00:46:13,000 --> 00:46:15,200
LOOK.

800
00:46:17,900 --> 00:46:20,100
WHAT?
SHH.

801
00:46:20,300 --> 00:46:20,900
I PREDICT

802
00:46:21,100 --> 00:46:22,700
THAT IN JUST A MOMENT

803
00:46:22,900 --> 00:46:25,700
WE WILL SEE A LADY
ON A RED BIKE,

804
00:46:26,500 --> 00:46:28,100
FOLLOWED BY A MAN
WITH FLOWERS

805
00:46:28,300 --> 00:46:30,900
AND A VOLKSWAGEN BEETLE

806
00:46:31,200 --> 00:46:32,400
WITH A DENTED FENDER.

807
00:46:32,600 --> 00:46:34,100
TRUMAN, PLEASE.

808
00:46:34,300 --> 00:46:36,700
Truman: LOOK.

809
00:46:40,200 --> 00:46:42,600
LADY...

810
00:46:43,500 --> 00:46:45,800
FLOWERS...

811
00:46:45,900 --> 00:46:48,300
Both: AND...

812
00:46:49,800 --> 00:46:51,500
TRUMAN, THIS IS SILLY.

813
00:46:51,700 --> 00:46:53,000
THERE IT IS!
THERE IT IS!

814
00:46:53,200 --> 00:46:56,100
  THERE'S THAT DENTED
BEETLE! YES!

815
00:46:56,400 --> 00:46:58,700
AAAAAAH!

816
00:46:58,700 --> 00:47:01,100
HA HA HA!

817
00:47:02,000 --> 00:47:04,900
DON'T YOU WANT TO KNOW
HOW I DID THAT?

818
00:47:04,900 --> 00:47:05,800
I'LL TELL YOU.

819
00:47:06,000 --> 00:47:06,800
THEY'RE ON A LOOP.

820
00:47:07,000 --> 00:47:08,400
THEY GO AROUND THE BLOCK.

821
00:47:08,700 --> 00:47:09,300
THEY COME BACK.

822
00:47:09,500 --> 00:47:10,600
THEY GO AROUND AGAIN.

823
00:47:10,800 --> 00:47:12,000
THEY JUST GO
ROUND AND ROUND.

824
00:47:12,200 --> 00:47:12,500
ROUND AND ROUND.

825
00:47:12,700 --> 00:47:15,800
I INVITED RITA AND MARLON
FOR A BARBECUE ON SUNDAY.

826
00:47:16,700 --> 00:47:17,200
I WON'T BE HERE
SUNDAY.

827
00:47:17,400 --> 00:47:20,100
AND I NEED YOU TO REMIND ME
THAT WE NEED MORE CHARCOAL.

828
00:47:20,300 --> 00:47:23,300
ARE YOU LISTENING
TO A WORD I'M SAYING?

829
00:47:23,600 --> 00:47:26,600
YOU'RE UPSET BECAUSE
YOU WANT TO GO TO FIJI.

830
00:47:27,500 --> 00:47:29,600
IS THAT IT?

831
00:47:29,800 --> 00:47:32,100
OK, OK, GO.

832
00:47:35,100 --> 00:47:38,000
I THINK YOU SHOULD SAVE
FOR A FEW MONTHS

833
00:47:38,000 --> 00:47:40,500
AND THEN GO. THERE.

834
00:47:40,800 --> 00:47:42,500
ARE YOU HAPPY NOW?

835
00:47:42,700 --> 00:47:45,400
I WANT TO GO TAKE A SHOWER.

836
00:47:46,200 --> 00:47:47,300
LET'S GO NOW.

837
00:47:47,500 --> 00:47:49,000
I'M READY TO GO NOW.
WHY WAIT?

838
00:47:49,200 --> 00:47:50,200
EARLY BIRD
GATHERS NO MOSS.

839
00:47:50,400 --> 00:47:53,300
ROLLING STONE CATCHES
THE WORM, RIGHT?

840
00:47:53,600 --> 00:47:54,700
[LAUGHS]

841
00:47:54,900 --> 00:47:57,700
Meryl: TRUMAN,
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

842
00:47:58,900 --> 00:48:01,100
OH!

843
00:48:02,700 --> 00:48:03,700
TRUMAN!

844
00:48:04,000 --> 00:48:06,800
WHERE SHALL WE GO?
WHERE SHALL WE GO?

845
00:48:07,700 --> 00:48:09,200
TRUMAN, WHERE
ARE WE GOING?

846
00:48:09,400 --> 00:48:12,500
I DON'T REALLY KNOW.
I GUESS I'M BEING SPONTANEOUS.

847
00:48:13,900 --> 00:48:15,100
SOMEBODY HELP ME!

848
00:48:15,300 --> 00:48:17,300
I'M BEING SPONTANEOUS!

849
00:48:17,500 --> 00:48:18,600
Meryl: TRUMAN.

850
00:48:18,800 --> 00:48:19,300
FORGET FIJI.

851
00:48:19,600 --> 00:48:21,800
CAN'T VERY WELL DRIVE
TO FIJI, CAN WE?

852
00:48:22,000 --> 00:48:24,200
NO.

853
00:48:24,700 --> 00:48:27,300
WHAT ABOUT
ATLANTIC CITY?

854
00:48:27,500 --> 00:48:29,400
OH, NO, YOU HATE
TO GAMBLE.

855
00:48:29,600 --> 00:48:30,400
THAT'S RIGHT,
I DO, DON'T I?

856
00:48:30,700 --> 00:48:32,300
SO WHY WOULD YOU WANT
TO GO THERE?

857
00:48:32,500 --> 00:48:33,600
BECAUSE I NEVER HAVE.

858
00:48:33,800 --> 00:48:36,700
THAT'S WHY PEOPLE
GO PLACES, ISN'T IT?

859
00:48:36,900 --> 00:48:39,900
TRUMAN, TRUMAN,
I THINK I'M GONNA THROW UP.

860
00:48:40,500 --> 00:48:42,700
ME, TOO.

861
00:48:49,900 --> 00:48:51,700
BLOCKED AT EVERY TURN.

862
00:48:51,900 --> 00:48:54,400
BEAUTIFULLY SYNCHRONIZED,
DON'T YOU AGREE?

863
00:48:54,600 --> 00:48:56,800
YOU'RE BLAMING ME
FOR THE TRAFFIC?

864
00:48:57,000 --> 00:48:59,300
SHOULD I?

865
00:49:04,900 --> 00:49:07,200
TRUMAN...

866
00:49:07,400 --> 00:49:09,400
LET'S GO HOME.

867
00:49:09,600 --> 00:49:10,300
YOU'RE RIGHT.

868
00:49:10,500 --> 00:49:11,800
WE COULD BE STUCK
HERE FOR HOURS.

869
00:49:12,000 --> 00:49:14,800
IT COULD BE LIKE THIS
ALL THE WAY TO ATLANTIC CITY.

870
00:49:15,000 --> 00:49:17,000
LET'S GO BACK.

871
00:49:17,200 --> 00:49:20,100
I'M SORRY. I DON'T KNOW
WHAT GOT INTO ME.

872
00:49:24,000 --> 00:49:26,700
Meryl: CAN YOU
PLEASE SLOW DOWN?

873
00:49:27,000 --> 00:49:29,500
YES, I CAN.

874
00:49:30,400 --> 00:49:31,900
TRUMAN! TRUMAN!
THAT'S OUR TURNOFF!

875
00:49:32,100 --> 00:49:33,200
I CHANGED MY MIND AGAIN.

876
00:49:33,400 --> 00:49:35,300
WHAT'S NEW ORLEANS LIKE
THIS TIME OF YEAR?

877
00:49:35,500 --> 00:49:38,100
MARDI GRAS! WHOO!
HA HA HA!

878
00:49:38,800 --> 00:49:40,500
[HONKING]

879
00:49:40,700 --> 00:49:43,000
WHOO!

880
00:49:43,100 --> 00:49:46,100
LOOK, MERYL, SAME ROAD,
NO CARS. IT'S MAGIC.

881
00:49:49,300 --> 00:49:49,900
HA HA HA!

882
00:49:50,100 --> 00:49:52,300
YOU LET ME OUT. YOU'RE
NOT RIGHT IN THE HEAD.

883
00:49:52,500 --> 00:49:54,700
YOU WANT TO DESTROY
YOURSELF, DO IT ON YOUR OWN.

884
00:49:54,900 --> 00:49:57,700
I THINK I'D LIKE
A LITTLE COMPANY.

885
00:50:04,200 --> 00:50:05,700
OH, TRUMAN...

886
00:50:05,900 --> 00:50:08,500
YOU KNEW
THIS WOULD HAPPEN.

887
00:50:09,000 --> 00:50:12,000
  YOU KNOW YOU CAN'T
DRIVE OVER WATER.

888
00:50:12,200 --> 00:50:15,000
LET'S GO HOME
WHERE YOU'LL FEEL SAFE.

889
00:50:17,800 --> 00:50:18,800
GIVE ME YOUR HAND.

890
00:50:19,000 --> 00:50:20,600
SWEETIE--

891
00:50:20,800 --> 00:50:22,600
DRIVE.

892
00:50:22,800 --> 00:50:23,800
TRUMAN!

893
00:50:24,000 --> 00:50:27,100
WE SHOULDN'T BE DOING THIS!
WE'RE BREAKING THE LAW!

894
00:50:27,300 --> 00:50:28,900
OH, MY!
YOU CAN DO IT!

895
00:50:29,100 --> 00:50:30,500
PLEASE, DON'T!

896
00:50:30,700 --> 00:50:32,500
YOU CAN MAKE IT!
TRUMAN!

897
00:50:32,700 --> 00:50:33,800
AAH! OH, WE'RE OVER!

898
00:50:34,000 --> 00:50:36,900
WE'RE OVER THE BRIDGE!
WE'RE OVER THE BRIDGE!

899
00:50:37,000 --> 00:50:37,300
WE'RE OVER?

900
00:50:37,500 --> 00:50:39,600
WE'RE OVER THE BRIDGE.
WE'RE OVER THE BRIDGE.

901
00:50:39,800 --> 00:50:40,600
WE'RE OVER!

902
00:50:40,800 --> 00:50:43,200
HA HA HA HA!

903
00:50:46,000 --> 00:50:47,900
TRUMAN! WHAT
ABOUT THAT SIGN?

904
00:50:48,100 --> 00:50:50,700
THEY'RE EXAGGERATING.
WE'LL BE FINE.

905
00:50:50,900 --> 00:50:53,800
  EXAGGERATING?
DO YOU BELIEVE THAT?

906
00:50:54,700 --> 00:50:57,000
[YELLING]

907
00:50:57,100 --> 00:51:00,000
OH, MY! OH, MY!
TRUMAN, WE'RE ON FIRE!

908
00:51:00,200 --> 00:51:01,200
IT'S OK.
WE'RE ON FIRE!

909
00:51:01,400 --> 00:51:03,600
  IT'S OK.
IT'S JUST SMOKE.

910
00:51:03,800 --> 00:51:05,100
YOU OK?
YES.

911
00:51:05,300 --> 00:51:07,200
WANT TO DO IT AGAIN?
NO!

912
00:51:07,400 --> 00:51:08,300
HA HA HA HA!

913
00:51:08,500 --> 00:51:11,100
TRUMAN, STOP!
OH, GOD!

914
00:51:12,200 --> 00:51:12,400
OH!

915
00:51:12,600 --> 00:51:14,400
SO, WHAT ARE WE GOING
TO DO FOR MONEY

916
00:51:14,600 --> 00:51:17,200
  WHEN WE GET
TO NEW ORLEANS?

917
00:51:17,400 --> 00:51:20,100
I HAVE MY SEAHAVEN
BANK CARD.

918
00:51:20,600 --> 00:51:23,700
WE'RE JUST GOING TO EAT
INTO OUR SAVINGS, IS THAT IT?

919
00:51:25,000 --> 00:51:27,600
I'M GOING TO HAVE TO CALL
YOUR MOTHER WHEN WE GET THERE.

920
00:51:27,800 --> 00:51:28,900
SHE'S GOING
TO BE WORRIED SICK.

921
00:51:29,100 --> 00:51:32,100
I DON'T KNOW HOW
SHE'S GOING TO TAKE THIS.

922
00:51:44,100 --> 00:51:45,500
WHAT NOW?

923
00:51:45,700 --> 00:51:48,600
Loudspeaker: RED ALERT!
THIS IS A RED ALERT!

924
00:51:49,100 --> 00:51:50,400
[PEOPLE YELLING]

925
00:51:50,600 --> 00:51:51,600
[CAR HORNS HONKING]

926
00:51:51,800 --> 00:51:54,400
TRUMAN, IT LOOKS LIKE
A LEAK AT THE PLANT.

927
00:51:54,600 --> 00:51:56,500
BACK UP! BACK UP!
LEAK AT THE PLANT.

928
00:51:56,700 --> 00:51:57,900
WE HAD TO SHUT HER DOWN.

929
00:51:58,100 --> 00:51:59,400
IS THERE
ANY WAY AROUND?

930
00:51:59,600 --> 00:52:00,400
WHOLE AREA'S
BEING EVACUATED.

931
00:52:00,600 --> 00:52:01,900
IS THERE
ANYTHING I CAN DO?

932
00:52:02,100 --> 00:52:02,600
NO, MA'AM.

933
00:52:02,800 --> 00:52:03,600
THANK YOU
FOR YOUR HELP.

934
00:52:03,800 --> 00:52:06,400
YOU'RE WELCOME,
TRUMAN.

935
00:52:07,400 --> 00:52:09,700
TRUMAN.

936
00:52:11,500 --> 00:52:13,500
TRUMAN! TRUMAN!

937
00:52:13,700 --> 00:52:15,700
TRUMAN, COME BACK!

938
00:52:15,900 --> 00:52:18,500
TRUMAN! TRUMAN!
STOP HIM!

939
00:52:19,100 --> 00:52:20,400
UNH!

940
00:52:20,600 --> 00:52:21,300
TRUMAN!

941
00:52:21,500 --> 00:52:23,200
[WHISTLES BLOWING]

942
00:52:23,400 --> 00:52:25,800
HEAD TO THE LEFT!

943
00:52:31,600 --> 00:52:33,900
AAH! AAH!

944
00:52:40,400 --> 00:52:42,700
STAY AWAY!

945
00:52:46,700 --> 00:52:47,700
UNH! AAH!

946
00:52:48,000 --> 00:52:50,200
UNH! NO!

947
00:52:50,600 --> 00:52:52,200
NO!

948
00:52:52,400 --> 00:52:54,000
Radio:
...NOW IN CUSTODY.

949
00:52:54,200 --> 00:52:56,700
[TRUMAN GROANING]

950
00:52:56,800 --> 00:52:59,200
THANK YOU BOTH SO MUCH
FOR YOUR HELP.

951
00:52:59,400 --> 00:53:00,800
I REALLY APPRECIATE IT.

952
00:53:01,000 --> 00:53:02,100
HE'S LUCKY TO BE
ALIVE, MA'AM.

953
00:53:02,300 --> 00:53:04,200
NEXT TIME, WE'LL HAVE
TO FILE CHARGES.

954
00:53:04,400 --> 00:53:05,800
I UNDERSTAND.

955
00:53:06,000 --> 00:53:07,900
THANKS AGAIN.

956
00:53:08,100 --> 00:53:10,500
GOOD NIGHT.

957
00:53:26,700 --> 00:53:29,500
LET ME GET YOU
SOME HELP, TRUMAN.

958
00:53:30,000 --> 00:53:32,500
YOU'RE NOT WELL.

959
00:53:33,800 --> 00:53:36,700
WHY DO YOU WANT
TO HAVE A BABY WITH ME?

960
00:53:38,000 --> 00:53:39,500
YOU CAN'T STAND ME.

961
00:53:39,700 --> 00:53:41,800
THAT'S NOT TRUE.

962
00:53:42,000 --> 00:53:44,300
[SCOFFS]

963
00:53:45,900 --> 00:53:48,600
WHY DON'T YOU LET ME FIX YOU
SOME OF THIS NEW MOCOCOA DRINK?

964
00:53:48,800 --> 00:53:51,100
ALL NATURAL COCOA BEANS
FROM THE UPPER SLOPES

965
00:53:51,300 --> 00:53:53,400
OF MOUNT NICARAGUA.
NO ARTIFICIAL SWEETENERS.

966
00:53:53,600 --> 00:53:56,400
WHAT THE HELL
ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

967
00:53:57,200 --> 00:53:58,100
WHO ARE YOU TALKING TO?

968
00:53:58,400 --> 00:54:01,400
I'VE TASTED OTHER COCOAS.
THIS IS THE BEST.

969
00:54:02,100 --> 00:54:05,200
WHAT THE HELL DOES THIS
HAVE TO DO WITH ANYTHING?

970
00:54:06,900 --> 00:54:08,300
TELL ME WHAT'S HAPPENING!

971
00:54:08,500 --> 00:54:11,500
YOU'RE HAVING A NERVOUS
BREAKDOWN, THAT'S WHAT.

972
00:54:11,900 --> 00:54:14,700
YOU'RE PART OF THIS,
AREN'T YOU?

973
00:54:17,500 --> 00:54:19,000
TRUMAN!
MERYL!

974
00:54:19,200 --> 00:54:21,800
YOU...ARE...SCARING ME!

975
00:54:22,200 --> 00:54:24,300
NO, YOU'RE SCARING ME, MERYL.

976
00:54:24,500 --> 00:54:27,300
WHAT ARE YOU GOING TO DO?
DICE ME?

977
00:54:28,200 --> 00:54:29,400
SLICE ME
AND PEEL ME?

978
00:54:29,600 --> 00:54:31,300
THERE ARE
SO MANY CHOICES!

979
00:54:31,500 --> 00:54:33,900
AAH! DO SOMETHING!

980
00:54:35,800 --> 00:54:37,100
WHAT?

981
00:54:37,400 --> 00:54:39,900
WHAT DID YOU SAY?
WHO ARE YOU TALKING TO?

982
00:54:40,100 --> 00:54:42,500
NOTHING. I DIDN'T
SAY ANYTHING.

983
00:54:42,700 --> 00:54:44,300
I DIDN'T
SAY ANYTHING.

984
00:54:44,500 --> 00:54:45,700
YOU SAID,
"DO SOMETHING."

985
00:54:45,900 --> 00:54:47,700
NO, I DIDN'T. I WASN'T
TALKING TO ANYBODY.

986
00:54:47,900 --> 00:54:49,000
TALK TO ME!

987
00:54:49,200 --> 00:54:49,600
[BANGING]

988
00:54:49,800 --> 00:54:51,500
I DON'T KNOW ANYTHING!
PLEASE STOP!

989
00:54:51,700 --> 00:54:53,800
STAY WHERE
YOU ARE!

990
00:54:54,000 --> 00:54:56,300
TRUMAN?

991
00:54:57,600 --> 00:54:58,400
TRUMAN?

992
00:54:58,600 --> 00:55:01,300
OH, THANK GOD!
OH, THANK GOD!

993
00:55:03,500 --> 00:55:05,300
[SOBBING]

994
00:55:05,500 --> 00:55:07,600
HOW CAN ANYONE
EXPECT ME

995
00:55:07,800 --> 00:55:10,600
TO CARRY ON UNDER
THESE CONDITIONS?

996
00:55:10,900 --> 00:55:13,100
IT'S UNPROFESSIONAL!

997
00:55:13,300 --> 00:55:15,700
SHH, IT'S OK.

998
00:55:17,600 --> 00:55:19,500
EVERYTHING'S
GONNA BE OK.

999
00:55:19,700 --> 00:55:20,600
OH, GOD!

1000
00:55:20,800 --> 00:55:23,400
IT'S ALL
GONNA BE FINE.

1001
00:55:25,300 --> 00:55:28,100
I DON'T KNOW WHAT
TO THINK, MARLON.

1002
00:55:31,600 --> 00:55:34,300
MAYBE I'M LOSING
MY MIND, BUT...

1003
00:55:37,800 --> 00:55:41,000
IT FEELS LIKE THE WHOLE WORLD
REVOLVES AROUND ME SOMEHOW.

1004
00:55:43,300 --> 00:55:46,200
THAT'S A LOT OF WORLD
FOR ONE MAN, TRUMAN.

1005
00:55:48,300 --> 00:55:51,100
SURE THAT'S NOT
WISHFUL THINKING?

1006
00:55:51,200 --> 00:55:52,800
YOU WISHING YOU'D MADE

1007
00:55:53,000 --> 00:55:55,000
SOMETHING MORE
OUT OF YOURSELF?

1008
00:55:55,200 --> 00:55:57,000
COME ON, WHO HASN'T
SAT IN THE JOHN,

1009
00:55:57,200 --> 00:56:00,400
  HAD AN IMAGINARY INTERVIEW
ON  SEAHAVEN TONIGHT?

1010
00:56:00,600 --> 00:56:01,800
WHO HASN'T WANTED
TO BE SOMEBODY?

1011
00:56:02,000 --> 00:56:05,000
THIS IS DIFFERENT.
EVERYBODY SEEMS TO BE IN ON IT.

1012
00:56:09,900 --> 00:56:13,000
I'VE BEEN YOUR BEST FRIEND
SINCE WE WERE 7 YEARS OLD.

1013
00:56:13,600 --> 00:56:15,500
THE ONLY WAY YOU AND I EVER
MADE IT THROUGH SCHOOL

1014
00:56:15,700 --> 00:56:18,700
WAS BY CHEATING OFF
EACH OTHER'S TEST PAPERS.

1015
00:56:19,700 --> 00:56:22,300
JESUS, THEY WERE IDENTICAL.

1016
00:56:23,500 --> 00:56:26,300
BUT I ALWAYS FELT SAFE
KNOWING THAT.

1017
00:56:27,100 --> 00:56:28,800
'CAUSE WHATEVER
THE ANSWER WAS,

1018
00:56:29,000 --> 00:56:32,000
WE WERE RIGHT TOGETHER
AND WE WERE WRONG TOGETHER.

1019
00:56:33,600 --> 00:56:36,600
REMEMBER WHEN I STAYED UP
ALL NIGHT IN YOUR TENT

1020
00:56:36,800 --> 00:56:39,700
'CAUSE YOU WANTED
TO PLAY NORTH POLE?

1021
00:56:40,200 --> 00:56:41,500
AND I GOT PNEUMONIA?

1022
00:56:41,700 --> 00:56:43,400
[LAUGHING]

1023
00:56:43,600 --> 00:56:45,300
YOU REMEMBER THAT?

1024
00:56:45,500 --> 00:56:48,400
YOU WERE OUT OF SCHOOL
FOR ABOUT A MONTH.

1025
00:56:53,800 --> 00:56:56,900
YOU'RE THE CLOSEST THING
I EVER HAD TO A BROTHER.

1026
00:57:03,900 --> 00:57:06,100
I KNOW THAT THINGS...

1027
00:57:06,300 --> 00:57:08,800
HAVEN'T REALLY WORKED
OUT FOR EITHER OF US

1028
00:57:09,000 --> 00:57:11,800
LIKE WE USED TO
DREAM THEY WOULD.

1029
00:57:11,900 --> 00:57:12,700
I KNOW THAT FEELING,

1030
00:57:12,900 --> 00:57:15,900
WHEN IT'S LIKE EVERYTHING'S
SLIPPING AWAY...

1031
00:57:16,800 --> 00:57:18,600
YOU DON'T WANT
TO BELIEVE IT,

1032
00:57:18,800 --> 00:57:21,700
SO YOU LOOK FOR ANSWERS
SOMEWHERE ELSE, BUT...

1033
00:57:26,400 --> 00:57:27,100
WELL...

1034
00:57:27,400 --> 00:57:30,200
Christof:
BUT, WELL, THE POINT IS...

1035
00:57:31,300 --> 00:57:34,200
I'D GLADLY WALK IN FRONT
OF TRAFFIC FOR YOU.

1036
00:57:38,000 --> 00:57:39,500
Marlon: WELL...

1037
00:57:39,700 --> 00:57:41,100
THE POINT IS,
I WOULD GLADLY

1038
00:57:41,300 --> 00:57:43,800
STEP IN FRONT OF TRAFFIC
FOR YOU, TRUMAN.

1039
00:57:44,000 --> 00:57:47,000
AND THE LAST THING
I'D EVER DO IS LIE TO YOU.

1040
00:57:49,800 --> 00:57:52,800
AND THE LAST THING
THAT I WOULD EVER DO...

1041
00:57:55,800 --> 00:57:58,200
IS LIE TO YOU.

1042
00:58:00,100 --> 00:58:02,900
I MEAN, THINK ABOUT IT,
TRUMAN.

1043
00:58:02,900 --> 00:58:05,600
IF EVERYBODY
IS IN ON IT...

1044
00:58:06,800 --> 00:58:09,500
I'D HAVE TO BE
IN ON IT, TOO.

1045
00:58:18,200 --> 00:58:21,000
I'M NOT IN ON IT,
TRUMAN, BECAUSE...

1046
00:58:21,800 --> 00:58:24,200
THERE IS NO "IT."

1047
00:58:27,100 --> 00:58:30,000
YOU WERE RIGHT ABOUT
ONE THING, THOUGH.

1048
00:58:31,100 --> 00:58:33,000
WHAT'S THAT?

1049
00:58:33,200 --> 00:58:36,000
THE THING THAT
STARTED ALL THIS.

1050
00:58:50,800 --> 00:58:53,500
YEP. I FOUND HIM
FOR YOU, TRUMAN.

1051
00:58:54,200 --> 00:58:56,400
THAT'S WHY
I CAME BY TONIGHT.

1052
00:58:56,600 --> 00:58:59,500
I'M SURE HE'S GOT
QUITE A STORY TO TELL.

1053
00:59:03,800 --> 00:59:06,200
GO TO HIM.

1054
00:59:11,500 --> 00:59:13,300
EASY ON THE FOG.

1055
00:59:13,500 --> 00:59:14,800
[KEYBOARD CLICKING]

1056
00:59:15,000 --> 00:59:17,500
STAND BY, CRANE CAM.

1057
00:59:18,200 --> 00:59:20,600
CRANE CAM.

1058
00:59:27,400 --> 00:59:29,900
BUTTON CAM 3.

1059
00:59:40,700 --> 00:59:43,300
I NEVER STOPPED BELIEVING.

1060
00:59:46,300 --> 00:59:49,100
Christof:
AND WIDE, CURB CAM 8.

1061
00:59:50,100 --> 00:59:52,500
MY SON! OH!

1062
00:59:52,800 --> 00:59:54,200
MOVE IN
FOR A CLOSEUP?

1063
00:59:54,400 --> 00:59:56,800
NO, NO, NO.

1064
00:59:57,300 --> 01:00:00,000
MOVE BACK AND...
FADE UP MUSIC.

1065
01:00:01,100 --> 01:00:03,500
[MUSIC SWELLS]

1066
01:00:07,000 --> 01:00:09,000
AND NOW GO IN CLOSE.

1067
01:00:09,200 --> 01:00:11,800
ALL THOSE
YEARS WASTED.

1068
01:00:12,000 --> 01:00:14,700
I'LL MAKE IT UP
TO YOU, SON.

1069
01:00:15,500 --> 01:00:17,400
I SWEAR.

1070
01:00:17,600 --> 01:00:20,000
[MUSIC SWELLS]

1071
01:00:23,800 --> 01:00:26,100
DAD.

1072
01:00:26,800 --> 01:00:29,000
YES!

1073
01:00:30,100 --> 01:00:32,500
[LAUGHING]

1074
01:00:37,300 --> 01:00:38,600
BRAVO.

1075
01:00:38,800 --> 01:00:41,600
THAT WAS A REALLY GREAT
EXPERIENCE.

1076
01:00:41,800 --> 01:00:42,400
Tech:
CONGRATULATIONS.

1077
01:00:42,600 --> 01:00:44,600
OK, QUIET DOWN.
LET'S CONCENTRATE.

1078
01:00:44,800 --> 01:00:47,400
Chloe:
THAT WAS GOOD WORK.

1079
01:00:47,600 --> 01:00:47,700
WHOO!

1080
01:00:47,900 --> 01:00:49,800
Tech: LET'S GET
SOME CHAMPAGNE UP HERE.

1081
01:00:50,000 --> 01:00:51,500
CONGRATULATIONS.

1082
01:00:51,700 --> 01:00:53,600
Moses: BRILLIANT, CHRISTOF.
JUST BRILLIANT.

1083
01:00:53,900 --> 01:00:56,600
Roman:
IT JUST BROKE MY HEART.

1084
01:01:00,100 --> 01:01:01,700
WELL DONE, EVERYONE!

1085
01:01:01,900 --> 01:01:04,100
BRAVO!

1086
01:01:20,500 --> 01:01:23,500
Announcer: 1.7 BILLION
WERE THERE FOR HIS BIRTH.

1087
01:01:27,500 --> 01:01:30,500
220 COUNTRIES TUNED IN
FOR HIS FIRST STEP.

1088
01:01:31,000 --> 01:01:34,000
THE WORLD STOOD STILL
FOR THAT STOLEN KISS,

1089
01:01:35,600 --> 01:01:38,200
AND AS HE GREW,
SO DID THE TECHNOLOGY.

1090
01:01:38,400 --> 01:01:39,100
AN ENTIRE HUMAN LIFE

1091
01:01:39,400 --> 01:01:42,400
RECORDED ON AN INTRICATE
NETWORK OF HIDDEN CAMERAS

1092
01:01:42,700 --> 01:01:45,700
AND BROADCAST LIVE AND
UNEDITED 24 HOURS A DAY,

1093
01:01:46,600 --> 01:01:49,600
7 DAYS A WEEK TO AN AUDIENCE
AROUND THE GLOBE.

1094
01:01:50,700 --> 01:01:53,300
COMING TO YOU NOW
FROM SEAHAVEN ISLAND,

1095
01:01:53,500 --> 01:01:56,500
ENCLOSED IN THE LARGEST
STUDIO EVER CONSTRUCTED,

1096
01:01:57,200 --> 01:01:58,800
AND ALONG WITH
THE GREAT WALL OF CHINA,

1097
01:01:59,000 --> 01:02:02,200
ONE OF ONLY 2 MANMADE STRUCTURES
VISIBLE FROM SPACE,

1098
01:02:03,600 --> 01:02:06,200
NOW IN ITS 30th GREAT YEAR,

1099
01:02:07,200 --> 01:02:09,500
IT'S...

1100
01:02:12,800 --> 01:02:15,100
WHAT A WEEK IT'S BEEN.
I DON'T KNOW ABOUT YOU--

1101
01:02:15,300 --> 01:02:16,900
I WAS ON PINS AND NEEDLES
THE ENTIRE TIME.

1102
01:02:17,100 --> 01:02:20,200
HELLO AND GOOD EVENING.
I'M YOUR HOST MIKE MICHAELSON,

1103
01:02:20,600 --> 01:02:21,900
  AND WELCOME TO  TRU-TALK,

1104
01:02:22,100 --> 01:02:23,800
OUR FORUM FOR ISSUES
GROWING OUT OF THE SHOW.

1105
01:02:24,000 --> 01:02:26,900
BUT TONIGHT,
SOMETHING VERY SPECIAL INDEED,

1106
01:02:27,500 --> 01:02:29,200
A RARE AND
EXCLUSIVE INTERVIEW

1107
01:02:29,400 --> 01:02:31,700
WITH THE SHOW'S
CONCEIVER AND CREATOR.

1108
01:02:31,900 --> 01:02:35,000
SO, COME WITH US NOW AS WE
GO LIVE TO THE LUNAR ROOM

1109
01:02:35,300 --> 01:02:38,200
ON THE 221st FLOOR
OF THE OMNI CAM ECHOSPHERE,

1110
01:02:38,800 --> 01:02:41,900
WHERE WE'LL FIND THE WORLD'S
GREATEST TELE-VISIONARY--

1111
01:02:42,900 --> 01:02:45,300
THE DESIGNER AND ARCHITECT
OF THE WORLD WITHIN A WORLD

1112
01:02:45,500 --> 01:02:48,300
THAT IS SEAHAVEN ISLAND--
CHRISTOF.

1113
01:02:48,400 --> 01:02:51,000
BEFORE WE BEGIN,
I'D LIKE TO THANK YOU

1114
01:02:51,200 --> 01:02:53,700
ON BEHALF OF OUR AUDIENCE
FOR GRANTING THIS INTERVIEW.

1115
01:02:53,900 --> 01:02:55,700
WE KNOW HOW DEMANDING
YOUR SCHEDULE IS,

1116
01:02:55,900 --> 01:02:59,000
AND WE ALL KNOW HOW JEALOUSLY
YOU GUARD YOUR PRIVACY.

1117
01:02:59,900 --> 01:03:02,600
THIS, SIR,
IS INDEED AN HONOR.

1118
01:03:02,800 --> 01:03:03,300
DON'T MENTION IT.

1119
01:03:03,500 --> 01:03:05,700
WELL, THE CATALYST FOR
THE RECENT DRAMATIC EVENTS

1120
01:03:05,900 --> 01:03:08,800
ON THE SHOW HAS BEEN
TRUMAN'S FATHER, KIRK,

1121
01:03:08,800 --> 01:03:10,300
AND HIS ATTEMPTS
TO INFILTRATE THE SHOW.

1122
01:03:10,500 --> 01:03:12,700
BUT BEFORE WE GET INTO THAT,
I THINK IT'S WORTH NOTING

1123
01:03:13,000 --> 01:03:16,100
THAT THIS IS NOT THE FIRST TIME
SOMEONE FROM THE OUTSIDE

1124
01:03:16,400 --> 01:03:17,500
HAS ATTEMPTED
TO REACH TRUMAN, IS IT?

1125
01:03:17,700 --> 01:03:20,100
Christof: WE HAVE HAD
CLOSE CALLS IN THE PAST.

1126
01:03:20,300 --> 01:03:23,000
Man: TRUMAN!
IT'S TELEVISION!

1127
01:03:23,300 --> 01:03:24,400
YES!

1128
01:03:24,600 --> 01:03:26,100
YES! I DID IT!

1129
01:03:26,300 --> 01:03:27,500
  I'M ON  THE TRUMAN SHOW!

1130
01:03:27,800 --> 01:03:30,200
Mike: BUT THERE'S NEVER
BEEN ANYTHING TO COMPARE

1131
01:03:30,400 --> 01:03:31,800
WITH THIS MOST RECENT
BREACH IN SECURITY--

1132
01:03:32,000 --> 01:03:35,000
THE FIRST INTRUDER TO BE
A FORMER CAST MEMBER.

1133
01:03:36,200 --> 01:03:37,100
A DEAD ONE AT THAT.

1134
01:03:37,300 --> 01:03:40,300
GOTTA SAY, WRITING KIRK
BACK IN--MASTERSTROKE.

1135
01:03:41,000 --> 01:03:44,100
SINCE KIRK STARTED THIS
CRISIS IN TRUMAN'S LIFE,

1136
01:03:44,100 --> 01:03:47,200
I CAME TO THE CONCLUSION
THAT ONLY HE COULD END IT.

1137
01:03:47,400 --> 01:03:49,900
TRUMAN! TRUMAN! NO!

1138
01:03:50,200 --> 01:03:51,300
[CONSTRUCTION NOISES]

1139
01:03:51,500 --> 01:03:52,400
THAT'S OFF LIMITS!

1140
01:03:52,600 --> 01:03:53,600
WHY? WHAT'S
OVER THERE?

1141
01:03:53,800 --> 01:03:55,700
NOTHING. IT'S DANGEROUS.
THAT'S ALL.

1142
01:03:55,900 --> 01:03:57,600
YOU'VE GOT TO KNOW
YOUR LIMITATIONS, TRUMAN.

1143
01:03:57,800 --> 01:04:00,200
Mike: BUT LET'S REMIND
VIEWERS EXACTLY WHY

1144
01:04:00,400 --> 01:04:02,600
DAD WAS WRITTEN OUT
IN THE FIRST PLACE.

1145
01:04:02,800 --> 01:04:04,600
Christof: AS TRUMAN GREW UP,
WE WERE FORCED

1146
01:04:04,800 --> 01:04:07,800
TO MANUFACTURE WAYS
TO KEEP HIM ON THE ISLAND.

1147
01:04:08,300 --> 01:04:09,900
I'D LIKE TO BE
AN EXPLORER,

1148
01:04:10,100 --> 01:04:11,600
LIKE THE GREAT
MAGELLAN.

1149
01:04:11,800 --> 01:04:12,300
YOU'RE TOO LATE.

1150
01:04:12,500 --> 01:04:15,300
THERE'S REALLY
NOTHING LEFT TO EXPLORE.

1151
01:04:15,500 --> 01:04:17,800
[SNARLING]

1152
01:04:19,400 --> 01:04:22,500
Christof: FINALLY, I CAME UP
WITH KIRK'S DROWNING.

1153
01:04:22,500 --> 01:04:23,200
Mike: MOST EFFECTIVE.

1154
01:04:23,400 --> 01:04:25,100
TRUMAN'S BEEN TERRIFIED
OF THE WATER EVER SINCE.

1155
01:04:25,300 --> 01:04:28,400
Christof: WHEN KIRK READ
THE SYNOPSIS OF THE EPISODE,

1156
01:04:28,400 --> 01:04:31,300
HE WAS DISAPPOINTED
TO SAY THE LEAST.

1157
01:04:31,800 --> 01:04:32,000
JESUS!

1158
01:04:32,200 --> 01:04:35,300
I'M SURE THAT'S WHAT CAUSED
HIM TO BREAK ONTO THE SET.

1159
01:04:35,600 --> 01:04:38,700
BUT HOW DO YOU INTEND TO
EXPLAIN HIS 22-YEAR ABSENCE?

1160
01:04:41,200 --> 01:04:41,600
AMNESIA.

1161
01:04:41,800 --> 01:04:44,800
BRILLIANT. LET'S TAKE
SOME VIEWER PHONE CALLS.

1162
01:04:45,300 --> 01:04:48,400
CHARLOTTE, NORTH CAROLINA,
YOU'RE ON WITH CHRISTOF.

1163
01:04:49,000 --> 01:04:51,500
Man: UH, YEAH,
HI, CHRISTOF.

1164
01:04:51,700 --> 01:04:54,800
I WAS WONDERING HOW MANY
CAMERAS YOU GOT IN THAT TOWN.

1165
01:04:55,300 --> 01:04:57,400
SOMEWHERE IN
THE VICINITY OF 5,000.

1166
01:04:57,600 --> 01:05:00,100
Man: THAT'S
A LOT OF CAMERAS.

1167
01:05:00,300 --> 01:05:03,100
REMEMBER, WE STARTED
WITH JUST ONE.

1168
01:05:03,300 --> 01:05:05,900
HE WAS CURIOUS
FROM BIRTH.

1169
01:05:08,000 --> 01:05:08,900
PREMATURE BY 2 WEEKS.

1170
01:05:09,100 --> 01:05:10,800
ALMOST AS IF HE COULDN'T
WAIT TO GET STARTED.

1171
01:05:11,000 --> 01:05:14,000
Mike: HIS EAGERNESS
TO LEAVE HIS MOTHER'S WOMB

1172
01:05:14,400 --> 01:05:15,700
WAS THE VERY REASON
HE WAS THE ONE SELECTED.

1173
01:05:15,900 --> 01:05:18,500
IN COMPETITION WITH 5 OTHER
UNWANTED PREGNANCIES,

1174
01:05:18,700 --> 01:05:21,700
THE CASTING OF A SHOW,
DETERMINED BY AN AIR DATE,

1175
01:05:21,700 --> 01:05:24,600
TRUMAN WAS THE ONE
WHO ARRIVED ON CUE.

1176
01:05:28,800 --> 01:05:32,000
Mike: INCIDENTALLY, I BELIEVE
TRUMAN IS THE FIRST CHILD

1177
01:05:32,000 --> 01:05:34,200
TO HAVE BEEN LEGALLY ADOPTED
BY A CORPORATION.

1178
01:05:34,400 --> 01:05:35,400
THAT'S CORRECT.

1179
01:05:35,600 --> 01:05:37,600
THE SHOW HAS GENERATED
ENORMOUS REVENUES NOW,

1180
01:05:37,800 --> 01:05:41,100
EQUIVALENT TO THE GROSS NATIONAL
PRODUCT OF A SMALL COUNTRY.

1181
01:05:41,600 --> 01:05:43,200
PEOPLE FORGET IT TAKES
THE POPULATION

1182
01:05:43,400 --> 01:05:44,900
OF AN ENTIRE COUNTRY TO
KEEP THE SHOW RUNNING.

1183
01:05:45,100 --> 01:05:46,800
SINCE THE SHOW IS ON
24-HOURS A DAY

1184
01:05:47,000 --> 01:05:50,300
WITHOUT COMMERCIAL INTERRUPTION,
ALL THOSE STAGGERING REVENUES

1185
01:05:50,900 --> 01:05:52,900
ARE GENERATED
BY PRODUCT PLACEMENT.

1186
01:05:53,100 --> 01:05:55,400
THAT'S TRUE. EVERYTHING
ON THE SHOW IS FOR SALE.

1187
01:05:55,700 --> 01:05:57,000
FROM THE ACTOR'S WARDROBE,
FOOD PRODUCTS,

1188
01:05:57,200 --> 01:05:58,100
TO THE VERY HOMES
THEY LIVE IN.

1189
01:05:58,300 --> 01:06:01,400
Mike: AND ALL OF IT AVAILABLE
IN THE TRUMAN CATALOG.

1190
01:06:01,500 --> 01:06:02,900
OPERATORS ARE STANDING BY.

1191
01:06:03,100 --> 01:06:04,700
CHRISTOF, LET ME ASK YOU,

1192
01:06:04,900 --> 01:06:07,900
WHY DO YOU THINK TRUMAN
HAS NEVER COME CLOSE

1193
01:06:08,300 --> 01:06:11,300
TO DISCOVERING THE TRUE NATURE
OF HIS WORLD UNTIL NOW?

1194
01:06:11,600 --> 01:06:13,500
WE ACCEPT THE REALITY
OF THE WORLD

1195
01:06:13,700 --> 01:06:15,600
WITH WHICH WE ARE
PRESENTED.

1196
01:06:15,800 --> 01:06:17,900
IT'S AS SIMPLE AS THAT.

1197
01:06:18,100 --> 01:06:19,800
THE HAGUE FOR CHRISTOF.

1198
01:06:20,100 --> 01:06:22,500
HELLO? THE HAGUE?

1199
01:06:23,600 --> 01:06:24,600
ALL RIGHT,
WE'VE LOST THAT CALL.

1200
01:06:24,900 --> 01:06:26,800
  LET'S GO TO HOLLYWOOD.
YOU'RE ON  TRU-TALK.

1201
01:06:27,000 --> 01:06:29,600
HI, CHRISTOF. I'D JUST
LIKE TO SAY ONE THING.

1202
01:06:29,900 --> 01:06:31,100
YOU'RE A LIAR
AND A MANIPULATOR,

1203
01:06:31,300 --> 01:06:33,200
AND WHAT YOU'VE DONE
TO TRUMAN IS SICK!

1204
01:06:33,400 --> 01:06:36,300
WELL, WE REMEMBER
THIS VOICE, DON'T WE?

1205
01:06:38,700 --> 01:06:39,700
HOW COULD WE FORGET?

1206
01:06:39,900 --> 01:06:41,200
Mike: LET'S GO
TO ANOTHER CALL.

1207
01:06:41,400 --> 01:06:44,100
NO, NO, NO.
IT'S FINE, MIKE.

1208
01:06:44,600 --> 01:06:47,700
I LOVE TO REMINISCE WITH
FORMER MEMBERS OF THE CAST.

1209
01:06:49,000 --> 01:06:50,900
SYLVIA...

1210
01:06:51,100 --> 01:06:54,200
AS YOU ANNOUNCED SO
MELODRAMATICALLY TO THE WORLD,

1211
01:06:54,500 --> 01:06:57,700
YOU THINK BECAUSE YOU BATTED
YOUR EYES AT TRUMAN ONCE...

1212
01:07:00,300 --> 01:07:01,900
FLIRTED WITH HIM...

1213
01:07:02,100 --> 01:07:03,400
STOLE A FEW MINUTES
OF AIR TIME WITH HIM...

1214
01:07:03,600 --> 01:07:06,900
TO THRUST YOURSELF AND YOUR
POLITICS INTO THE LIMELIGHT...

1215
01:07:07,800 --> 01:07:08,900
THAT YOU KNOW HIM?

1216
01:07:09,100 --> 01:07:10,900
THAT YOU KNOW
WHAT'S RIGHT FOR HIM?

1217
01:07:11,100 --> 01:07:14,200
YOU REALLY THINK YOU'RE
IN A POSITION TO JUDGE HIM?

1218
01:07:14,200 --> 01:07:16,300
WHAT RIGHT DO YOU HAVE
TO TAKE A BABY

1219
01:07:16,500 --> 01:07:19,400
AND TURN HIS LIFE INTO
SOME KIND OF MOCKERY?

1220
01:07:19,500 --> 01:07:22,200
DON'T YOU EVER
FEEL GUILTY?

1221
01:07:23,100 --> 01:07:26,100
I HAVE GIVEN TRUMAN A CHANCE
